# Phase 10: Engagement & Social Hub

Resolving issues with video plays (view counts) and implementing a robust, real-time social layer for VibeStream.

## User Review Required

> [!IMPORTANT]
> This update involves running database migrations which will enable atomic incrementing of views and likes. This ensures data consistency even under high traffic.

## Proposed Changes

### Database Layer
- [NEW] [setup-engagement.sql](file:///C:/GOLive/scripts/setup-engagement.sql): Tables for `likes` and `comments`.
- [NEW] [engagement-rpcs.sql](file:///C:/GOLive/scripts/engagement-rpcs.sql): Atomic RPC functions:
  - `increment_view_count`: Simple +1 for views.
  - `toggle_like`: Atomic like/unlike that updates both the `likes` table and `videos.likes_count`.
  - `increment_hype_count`: Updated for better null handling.

---

### Frontend: Watch Page Refinement
#### [MODIFY] [WatchClient.tsx](file:///C:/GOLive/app/watch/[id]/WatchClient.tsx)
- **View Counting**: Add `useEffect` to trigger `increment_view_count` RPC on video load (debounced or on initial play).
- **Social Logic**:
  - Update [handleLike](file:///C:/GOLive/app/watch/%5Bid%5D/WatchClient.tsx#100-128) to use the `toggle_like` RPC for guaranteed consistency.
  - Implement the "Share" button using `navigator.clipboard`.
- **Engagement Display**: Ensure `likes_count` from the DB is prioritized over the bot-driven `target_likes`.

#### [MODIFY] [CommentSection.tsx](file:///C:/GOLive/components/CommentSection.tsx)
- Verify real-time channel binding.
- Ensure profile normalization handles both single and array returns from Supabase Join.

## Verification Plan

### Automated Verification
- Run [scripts/migrate.ts](file:///C:/GOLive/scripts/migrate.ts) for both SQL files.
- Verify RPC connectivity via small test script.

### Manual Verification
- Open a video, refresh, and confirm `view_count` increments.
- Click Like and verify the count updates and persists across refreshes.
- Post a comment and verify it appearing instantly for other potential sessions.
- Click Share and confirm the URL is copied to the clipboard.
